---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base";

const meta = {
	title: "CV",
	description: "Alejandro Rico's CV",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<div class="max-w-2xl">
		<section class="mb-12">
			<p class="mb-4">
				Product and data lead for large-scale games. 8+ years using analytics, experimentation, and ML to shape product strategy. Independently built consumer apps with 130k+ downloads.
			</p>
			<p class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
				<a href="mailto:aljrico@gmail.com" class="cactus-link">aljrico@gmail.com</a>
				<a href="https://github.com/aljrico" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cactus-link">github.com/aljrico</a>
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="title mb-4 text-xl">Experience</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-6">
				<li>
					<div class="font-semibold">Uplift Games</div>
					<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Senior Data Analyst · 2022–present · Remote</div>
					<p class="mt-1">Own analytics for Roblox's most-visited game, with 2M peak CCU and 40B+ visits. Built the analytics stack and established the A/B testing practice from scratch. Led forecasting, economy balancing, and exploit detection. Partner with product and game teams on live ops, economy design, and growth.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="font-semibold">Mango Solutions</div>
					<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Senior Data Scientist · 2019–2022 · London</div>
					<p class="mt-1">Technical lead for enterprise analytics tools built with R and Shiny. Set coding and technical standards and mentored junior developers. Spoke at R conferences, ran workshops, and represented the technical side in sales and scoping.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="font-semibold">Supersolid</div>
					<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Product Manager & Data Analyst · 2019 · London</div>
					<p class="mt-1">Hybrid role: owned product strategy and analytics for the flagship game (100k DAU). Reported to CEO, led cross-functional prioritisation, built the A/B testing practice.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="font-semibold">Cass Business School</div>
					<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Research Scientist · 2018–2019 · London</div>
					<p class="mt-1">High-performance simulations (R + C++) and ML research applied to stock market prediction.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div class="font-semibold">Socialpoint</div>
					<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Junior Data Scientist · 2018 · Barcelona</div>
					<p class="mt-1">A/B test analysis, LTV modelling, and ML for mobile games with 100M+ downloads.</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="title mb-4 text-xl">Independent Products</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-3">
				<li><a href="/apps/tiny-crimes" class="cactus-link">Tiny Crimes</a>: built and operate a cross-platform logic game that reached 30,000 downloads in its first two months and now serves about 3,000 daily active users. Built in Flutter around a procedural engine that generates and verifies uniquely solvable puzzles.</li>
				<li><a href="/apps/cookie-empire" class="cactus-link">Cookie Empire</a>: built and operate an iOS idle game with 100k+ downloads and a Discord community of nearly 1,000 players. Own product, SwiftUI development, monetisation, live ops, analytics, and A/B testing.</li>
				<li><a href="/apps/test-dgt" class="cactus-link">Test DGT</a>: built and shipped a driving theory app with 2,600+ illustrated questions, adaptive lessons, exam simulations, and offline support. Engineered a multi-agent content pipeline for generation, fact-checking, adjudication, and quality control.</li>
				<li><a href="/apps/flama-coach" class="cactus-link">Mossos Coach</a>: built a subscription study app with 3,500+ questions, adaptive practice, exam simulations, and offline support. Created the content pipeline from official legal texts through production delivery.</li>
				<li>Earlier projects: <a href="/apps/coffee-galley" class="cactus-link">Coffee Galley</a>, a fully automated Shopify fulfilment app built in R; <a href="/apps/match-tile-mini" class="cactus-link">Match Tile: Mini</a>; <a href="/apps/pizza-clicker" class="cactus-link">Pizza Clicker</a>; and two open-source R visualisation packages.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="title mb-4 text-xl">Skills</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-500">
				<li><span class="font-semibold text-textColor">Product:</span> strategy, experimentation, retention, monetisation, live ops</li>
				<li><span class="font-semibold text-textColor">Data:</span> SQL, BigQuery, ClickHouse, Looker, R, Python, machine learning</li>
				<li><span class="font-semibold text-textColor">Engineering:</span> Swift, SwiftUI, Flutter, TypeScript, C++, AI and agent systems</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2 class="title mb-4 text-xl">Education</h2>
			<ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
				<li>MSc Data Science & Mathematical Modelling, UAB</li>
				<li>MSc Financial Mathematics, UAB</li>
				<li>BSc Physics, UAB</li>
				<li>International Certificate in Wealth and Investment Management, CISI</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
